  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine if Selective Adsorption System for Removal of
      Bacterial Toxins (S.A.F.E.BT) therapy is effective in the treatment of severe sepsis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Is extracorporeal treatment effective in the treatment of sepsis
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
  <overall_status>Terminated</overall_status>
  <why_stopped>
    Study stopped for operational futility. Due to very small numbers of subjects, insufficient
    data was available for results to provide meaningful conclusions.
  </why_stopped>
